    "text": "You've spotted a real mismatch: the goal is scored on a recovery metric with a green zone at 67%, and manual logging produces no recovery score, HRV, or resting heart rate to measure it — so I can't track progress on that number for you. What I can coach is the inputs that move it. You logged 413 minutes of sleep last night, about 6.9 h; recovery improves most reliably from slightly longer and very consistent sleep, hard sessions spaced with genuinely easy days between them, and limited late-evening alcohol. If you want the score itself, a ring or wrist wearable closes the gap. Otherwise, log sleep plus a simple morning energy rating daily and we'll trend that as your stand-in.",
